Also‚Ä¶ @Fino The Golden üêï ‚Äòs kid energy in this üòÜ ‚ùÑÔ∏è BASE LAYERS  Crucial to keep you warm & wick up sweat. I love my Helly Hansen base layer top & I wear it all the time. My go-to leggings for are @lululemon Wunder Train, this Espresso colour is üëåüèº ‚ùÑÔ∏è THICK SOCKS  I usually get mine from @Roots or @üüß Mark‚Äôs  ‚ùÑÔ∏è MID-LAYER This can be a knit, fleece, sweater etc. Just something that will keep you toasty. I love this North Face fleece & it‚Äôs perfect for skiing & dog walks.  ‚ùÑÔ∏è WINTER/SNOW BOOTS  @Baffinworldwide snow boots are the warmest I‚Äôve found & they have an insulated inner lining to keep your toes extra toasty even in -20C temps. These are the CHLOE boots.  ‚ùÑÔ∏è WINTER COAT  I LOVE my new @RUDSAK coat & their winter gear is beautiful. It‚Äôs functional, super warm, minimalistic & really high quality. This is the MAVE M PUFFER in Cement.  ‚ùÑÔ∏è WARMERS  I love my Rudsak ski mittens (I find mittens keep my hands warmer than regular gloves) & they even have a little pocket to slip in a hand warmer. Roots always have great knit hats.
